In Flutter, Column and Row are layout widgets used to arrange multiple child widgets vertically or horizontally.

syntax
Column(
  mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
  crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
  children: [
    Text('Hello'),
    Text('Flutter'),
    Icon(Icons.star),
  ],
)
| Property               | Description                                                           |
| ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **children**           | List of widgets to display vertically.                                |
| **mainAxisAlignment**  | Controls vertical alignment (top, center, bottom, spaceAround, etc.). |
| **crossAxisAlignment** | Controls horizontal alignment (start, center, end, stretch).          |
| **mainAxisSize**       | Defines how much vertical space the Column takes (min or max).        |

Column(
  mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
  crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.center,
  children: [
    Text('Welcome'),
    Icon(Icons.favorite, color: Colors.red),
    ElevatedButton(onPressed: () {}, child: Text('Click Me')),
  ],
)

The Row widget arranges its children horizontally (from left to right).

Row(
  mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.spaceEvenly,
  crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.center,
  children: [
    Icon(Icons.home),
    Icon(Icons.search),
    Icon(Icons.settings),
  ],
)

combination both
Column(
  children: [
    Text('Top Section'),
    Row(
      mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
      children: [
        Icon(Icons.star, color: Colors.yellow),
        Icon(Icons.star, color: Colors.yellow),
        Icon(Icons.star, color: Colors.yellow),
      ],
    ),
    Text('Bottom Section'),
  ],
)
